                    <div class="input-group-append">
                        <input type="submit" value="Subscribe" class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm sends-events" data-ga-category="CTA" data-ga-action="email_focus" data-ga-label="c4087a59c7" />
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div style="position: absolute; left: -5000px;"><input type="text" name="b_c49dc69f492af7f2727860d0b_c4087a59c7" tabindex="-1" value=""></div>

            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>A wealth of experiences, privilege included, impact perspective and no perspective should be considered invalid because of a single factor. This semester, I hope that white people will be more comfortable talking about race, straight men will be more comfortable talking about gender and sexuality, and wealthy people will be more comfortable talking about economic issues like income inequality. More Duke students talking. I also hope that each one of those aforementioned groups will weigh the effect that privilege has had on their beliefs, as all groups should consider how experience informs worldview.</p>
<p>Duke students, check your privilege—but do not silence yourselves.</p>
<p><em>Locquere meloria silentio. </em>Say something better than silence.</p>
<p><em>Jacob Weiss is a Trinity senior. His column, "not jumping to any conclusions" runs on alternate Fridays.</em></p>

